===Etymology===
Middle English ''plese'' < Middle French ''[[plaisir]]'' < Latin ''[[placere]]'' ('to please', 'to seem good').

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/pliːz/}}

===Verb===
'''to please''' ([[pleases]], [[pleasing]], [[pleased]])

#''(transitive)'' To make [[happy]] or satisfy; to give [[pleasure]].

====Synonyms====
*[[satisfy]]
*[[be]] [[pleasing]] to

====Antonyms====
